premise_source_doc_sentence: Nicomachus of Gerasa  (  Νικόμαχος c. 60 -- c. 120 CE  )  was an important ancient mathematician best known for his works Introduction to Arithmetic and Manual of Harmonics in Greek .
He was born in Gerasa , in the Roman province of Syria  (  now Jerash , Jordan  )  , and was strongly influenced by Aristotle .
He was a Neopythagorean , who wrote about the mystical properties of numbers .

In 383 BC , with war having again broken out with the Carthaginians , Leptines once more took an active part in supporting his brother , and commanded the right wing of the Syracusan army in the battle near Cronium , around 375 BC .
Yan , Marquis of Tian  (  ; died 375 BC  )  was from 383 to 375 BC ruler of the State of Qi , a major power during the Warring States period of ancient China .
Leptines  (  Λεπτίνης died 375 BC  )  was a military leader from Syracuse , Sicily , active during his brother , Dionysius the Elder 's wars .

c. 375 BC  )  was the father of Aristotle .
